main event: A civilian observed a bright object similar to a star that disappeared over the horizon in Holmcraft, Minnesota on August 23, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 5 minutes before disappearing,The flight course was initially reported as 3E to North,The conclusion of the report suggested it may have been the satellite ECHO II,There were no other air traffic in the area at the time of the sighting,The object was described as brighter than a star.
sighted object: a bright object resembling a star
